<p>Isotope is an Event Emitter. You can bind listeners to events with the <a href="methods.html#on">on</a> and <a href="methods.html#off">off</a> methods.</p>

```js
var $container = $('#container').isotope({...});
var iso = new Isotope( elem );

function onArrange() {
  console.log('layout done');
}
// bind event listener
$container.isotope( 'on', 'arrangeComplete', onArrange );
// un-bind event listener
$container.isotope( 'off', 'arrangeComplete', onArrange );
// bind event listener to be triggered just once
$container.isotope( 'once', 'arrangeComplete', function() {
  console.log('arrange done, just this one time');
});
```


<h2>arrangeComplete</h2>

``` js
$container.isotope( 'on', 'arrangeComplete', function( filteredItems ) {} )
// or with vanilla JS
iso.on( 'arrangeComplete', function( filteredItems ) {} )
// or with jQuery
```

